agent_answer:
To change your Zsh theme to 'agnoster', follow these steps:
1. Open your `~/.zshrc` file in a text editor of your choice.
2. Find the line that starts with `ZSH_THEME` and change it to `ZSH_THEME="agnoster"`.
3. Save the changes and exit the editor.
4. Install a Powerline or a Nerd Font to ensure the special characters render correctly. You can find patched fonts [here](https://github.com/powerline/fonts) or patch your own using [fontpatcher](https://github.com/powerline/fontpatcher).
5. Optionally, set `DEFAULT_USER` to your regular username in the `~/.zshrc` file to hide the “user@hostname” info when you’re logged in as yourself on your local machine, or add `prompt_context(){}` to always hide it.
6. Reload your Zsh configuration by running `source ~/.zshrc` in your terminal.

task.question: Find the wiki page of ohmyzsh on GitHub and tell me how to change the theme of zsh to agnoster.
task.answer: edit the .zshrc file and set the ZSH_THEME variable to "agnoster"
